quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  17,78,"Maintain the prayer [during the period] from the sun’s decline till the darkness of the night, and [observe particularly] the dawn recital. Indeed the dawn recital is attended [by angels]"
  17,79,"And keep vigil for a part of the night, as a supererogatory [devotion] for you. It may be that your Lord will raise you to a praiseworthy station"
  17,80,"And say, ‘My Lord! ‘Admit me with a worthy entrance, and bring me out with a worthy departure, and render me a favourable authority from Yourself.’"
  17,81,"And say, ‘The truth has come, and falsehood has vanished. Indeed falsehood is bound to vanish.’"
  17,82,We send down in the Quran that which is a cure and mercy for the faithful; and it increases the wrongdoers only in loss
  17,83,"When We bless man, he is disregardful and turns aside; but when an ill befalls him, he is despondent"
  17,84,"Say, ‘Everyone acts according to his character. Your Lord knows best who is better guided with regard to the way.’"